        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="2">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage, personal injury, or death, park the vehicle on a flat level surface,
                        set the parking brake, turn the engine off, and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
                <warning>
                    <para>Batteries expel explosive gases. Keep sparks, flames, burning cigarettes, or other ignition
                        sources away at all times. Always wear safety glasses and a face shield when working near
                        batteries to avoid personal injury or death.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0647034" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0647034.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                         scalefitheight="296px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Battery Box Support Angle Installation</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. BATTERY BOX</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SUPPORT ANGLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. RIVET</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. 'V' SUPPORT RAIL (ON BOTTOM OF BATTERY BOX)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean the bottom corners of the battery box, inside and outside, in the areas where the
                    support angles are to be added (Figure 4).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the bottom of the battery box is currently deformed or has started to separate from
                    the sides, use common sheet metal repair practices to return the bottom to its original position
                    before continuing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>1. When installed each support angle must fit flush with the side and bottom of the battery
                        box. To accomplish this each support angle must be located so that one of its notches lines up
                        with the 'V' support rail on the bottom of the battery box (Figure 4).
                    </para>
                    <para>2. The location of the battery box "V" support rail on the bottom of the battery box is not
                        located consistently; therefore modifying the 2" notch in part 2592801C2 may be necessary to get
                        a flush fit between the support angles and the bottom of the battery box. Prime and paint pieces
                        before installing them.
                    </para>
                    <para>3. RE models may not always have clearance for the rivet gun to fit between the engine
                        compartment and the battery box; therefore, purchase and install (8) Grade 8 1/4" diameter X
                        1.00" long bolts and lock nuts. Locate the bolt heads on the inside of the battery box.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0747011" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0747011.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="208px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position a support angle on the battery box as indicated (Figure 4). Using the support
                    angle as a template, drill the eight holes required to secure it to the battery box.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using the provided rivets, and a rivet tool capable of installing 1/4 inch rivets,
                    secure the support angle to the battery box.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Repeat procedure to attach the second support angle to the other side of the battery
                    box.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean and prep the new parts and areas of the battery box affected by the
                    installation.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Prime, repaint and re-undercoat the affected areas, as necessary.</para>
            </step1>
